Reasoning: The paper discusses the advancement of deep learning in pattern recognition tasks, specifically in visual recognition of object categories, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also focuses on evaluating artificial systems for tasks that are sensitive to individual differences, which suggests a human-centered approach and falls under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of a probabilistic model and computation method for judgment suggests a machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) approach. Finally, the task of ranking image pairs according to material attributes of objects suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) as a possible sub-category.
